You must execute the daily digest update workflow in this exact order.

**Context:** the daily digest is covered by **OpenClaw (Qwen 3.5 cloud)** in the fixed **14:00** Spain time window (**Europe/Madrid**). This prompt is the assembly step in Cursor within that same daily flow.

1) Archive the current digest:
- Take the current `index.html` (it is likely yesterday's digest).
- Read the digest date shown in the current `index.html` header (the digest being archived), and use that exact date for the archive filename in `old/YYYY_MM_DD.html`.
- Copy its full HTML content into that new dated file inside `old/` (following the same naming convention as existing files in `old/`).
- Important: when that current `index.html` is moved/copied into `old/`, update its footer link `Ver ediciones antiguas` (the link at the end of `index.html`, currently `href="old.html"`) so it becomes `href="../old.html"` in the archived file.
- Important: when that current `index.html` is moved/copied into `old/`, update the stylesheet path in `<head>` from `href="style.css"` to `href="../style.css"` in the archived file.
- Register that new archived file by adding its route/link entry into `old.html`, consistent with how previous archived digests are listed.
- Update the footer link inside the moved archived file so it points correctly to `old.html` from `old/` (`"old.html"` -> `"../old.html"`).

2) Reset `index.html` to the base template:
- Delete ALL content currently inside `index.html`.
- Paste the full HTML template from `agent/context/htmlTemplate.md` into `index.html`.

3) Insert prepared articles into the new digest:
- Open `agent/articlesHtml.md` for the HTML: take only the `<article>...</article>` blocks (ignore comments or short instructions at the top of that file).
- Open `agent/context/articles.md` for **context only**: use it to order the articles (section order and strict per-section newsletter order).
- Move the HTML article content from `articlesHtml.md` into `index.html` in that order.
- Handle links in two layers:
  - Newsletter-level (`Web link`): keep one top-level link per newsletter `<article>`; if missing, use the fallback mapping in `agent/prompt1CorreoToResumen.md` (lines 10-43).
  - Article-level (per-item): for multi-story newsletters, keep each concrete link for each listed item.
- Ensure every article keeps its concrete source link when available.
- The multi-story newsletters that require one per-item link are exactly: 1440, The Objective, The Substack Post, TLDR, Superhuman, and HackerNoon.
- For those newsletters, preserve the specific URL of each referenced story/item instead of collapsing to a generic homepage, and place the respective `Link` inside each corresponding `<li>` whenever the article body is rendered as a list.
- In each `<article>`, place the link right after the article description/content paragraph as a clear CTA, preferably:
```html
        <p><a href="https://..." target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Link</a></p>
```
- If an `<article>` from `agent/articlesHtml.md` does not include an article link (`<p><a href=...`), append one at the end of that `<article>` using the corresponding base URL from `agent/prompt1CorreoToResumen.md` (lines 10-41), with this format:
```html
        <p><a href="https://join1440.com/digest/2026-04-15" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer">Link.</a></p>
```
- After moving the HTML articles into `index.html`, DELETE those moved `<article>...</article>` blocks from `agent/articlesHtml.md`. You may leave the file empty or keep only the top HTML comment line if present.

4) Finalize daily metadata:
- Update the date in `index.html` to today's date.
- Update/rebuild the digest index in `index.html` so it matches the final rendered sections and article anchors.
- If any section has zero articles after assembly, do not include that section in `index.html` (neither in the index nor as a section header).

5) Cleanup run artifacts:
- After successfully rebuilding `index.html` and moving consumed articles, DELETE the `runs/` directory for this daily execution.

6) Commit and publish to GitHub:
- After finishing all previous steps, run:
```bash
git add .
git commit -m "Digest YYYY-MM-DD"
git push origin main
```
- Replace `YYYY-MM-DD` with the current day date (for example, `Digest 2026-04-16`).
- Under NO circumstances add extra text in the commit message (e.g., "Made with Cursor" or similar).
- The commit message must be EXCLUSIVELY this format: `Digest YYYY-MM-DD` (for example, `Digest 2026-04-16`).

Task summary:
1) Archive the current `index.html` into `old/YYYY_MM_DD.html` using the archived digest date from the current `index.html` header.
2) Update `old.html`.
3) Rebuild `index.html` with template + ordered articles + today's date and index.
4) Delete `runs/`.
